WEBVTT

00:31.266 --> 00:37.716
Well, according to the Bible, the empty tomb is literally the heartbeat of our faith.

00:38.637 --> 00:46.770
I mean, the fact of what we celebrate right now this weekend, the resurrection is our only source of hope.

00:46.910 --> 01:00.210
And boy, God really inspired Paul in a specific way to make this clear in both the negative and the positive in 1 Corinthians chapter 15, starting with verse 17.

01:00.994 --> 01:06.980
Hall wrote, and if Christ has not been raised, your faith is futile.

01:07.500 --> 01:08.921
I mean, you're still in your sins.

01:09.702 --> 01:16.188
Then those also who have fallen asleep, who are dead, having believed in Christ, are lost, it means nothing.

01:17.109 --> 01:22.874
If only for this life we have hope in Christ, we're of all people most to be pitied.

01:23.375 --> 01:30.962
If we live a life believing in Jesus and looking forward to his hope, and he never walked out of the tomb,

01:31.618 --> 01:32.479
It's a joke.

01:33.340 --> 01:40.210
It's a waste, but then Paul said, put that fear and anxiety and doubt to bed.

01:41.111 --> 01:48.000
Because Christ has indeed been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep.

01:48.521 --> 01:52.967
He is risen, it is true, and you can find your hope in it.

01:57.453 --> 01:59.475
But here's the reality we have to confess.

01:59.576 --> 02:01.458
If the resurrection of Jesus

02:01.762 --> 02:08.893
is not true, then all of the teachings and all of the promises of Jesus are worthless.

02:09.794 --> 02:18.528
But as Paul stated it, the good news that we can embrace on this Easter Sunday is that it is true.

02:19.109 --> 02:23.235
And any of you who may be skeptical about that, we get it.

02:23.636 --> 02:24.437
You're welcome.

02:24.837 --> 02:25.939
We've all been there.

02:25.979 --> 02:30.386
But you need to do just a little bit of investigation.

02:30.562 --> 02:37.873
Don't buy the party line that this is just a fairy tale, that you can't believe this.

02:37.893 --> 02:39.435
There's no way this happened.

02:39.516 --> 02:42.240
That kind of thing doesn't go on in the world.

02:42.680 --> 02:44.563
Do a little deep dive.

02:45.324 --> 02:46.546
There are books written about it.

02:46.566 --> 02:47.908
I've given talks about it.

02:48.790 --> 02:55.440
But it's not a blind leap of faith to believe that Jesus rose from the dead.

02:55.580 --> 02:59.506
On the contrary, it's historically difficult

02:59.650 --> 03:00.832
to dismiss.

03:01.112 --> 03:07.500
In fact, it's the most rational explanation to all of the history that we have about this event.

03:08.642 --> 03:13.768
All of the disciples ran for fear of their lives, were cowards.

03:13.889 --> 03:21.438
And in spite of committing to follow Jesus, they ran away from Jesus when he was betrayed and being hauled by the government to be crucified.

03:21.498 --> 03:22.720
I mean, these were cowards.

03:23.721 --> 03:27.346
And then somehow, amazingly, after his death,

03:28.994 --> 03:30.456
which should have caused them more fear.

03:30.736 --> 03:31.778
We were good to run.

03:31.818 --> 03:38.688
They could kill us too, but after he died, all of a sudden they lost their fear and they became fearless.

03:39.529 --> 03:41.371
All of a sudden, they weren't running away.

03:41.452 --> 03:49.683
They were running into trouble and they were running into trouble, declaring the reality of the name of Jesus, which could and ultimately did get them killed.

03:50.144 --> 03:51.966
What led to that change?

03:53.769 --> 03:54.610
A lie?

03:56.194 --> 04:03.906
They stole the body and then wanted to convince people he was real, and they all died, and because of that, no, it doesn't make sense.

04:05.228 --> 04:14.943
But I think even more important than the disciples, who were Jesus' allies, who were Jesus' friends, you can see them wanting maybe to build up his story.

04:14.983 --> 04:22.153
But the guy that just wrote, if the resurrection didn't happen, it's worthless to follow Jesus, but you can count on it and happen.

04:22.174 --> 04:25.138
Not only did he live at the time that Jesus lived,

04:25.890 --> 04:28.453
He was trained as a leader of the Jews.

04:28.593 --> 04:31.117
He was one of the smart guys of that culture.

04:32.578 --> 04:41.730
And he started out despising Christ, celebrating his death and trying to destroy any memory that he had ever lived.

04:42.190 --> 04:51.282
He hauled people and threw them into prison, destroyed their lives, and even was party to killing people for simply naming Jesus Christ.

04:51.322 --> 04:54.546
And then one day, he changed.

04:55.618 --> 04:59.743
And he says, you know the Jesus that I dismissed?

05:01.205 --> 05:04.909
I met him alive, and he's changed my life.

05:05.650 --> 05:10.436
And the rest of his life was lived for the hope of Jesus, even though it destroyed his life.

05:10.496 --> 05:11.518
He was thrown in prison.

05:11.578 --> 05:16.944
He was beaten to a pulp multiple times, and he ultimately died for this proclamation.

05:17.345 --> 05:21.089
What turns an enemy to a proponent?

05:22.872 --> 05:24.754
There's only one really

05:24.930 --> 05:28.295
rational explanation, this guy met the living Jesus.

05:30.578 --> 05:31.899
But I'm not here to convince you.

05:32.821 --> 05:34.883
I'm here to share what should be the impact.

05:36.646 --> 05:42.374
For those of us who do embrace the idea of the resurrection, we're excited about singing these songs in this holiday.

05:42.734 --> 05:49.944
For those of us who really do believe it, there's an important question we should be asking ourselves, and that's simply this.

05:50.444 --> 05:51.666
What if it's true?

05:53.186 --> 05:56.291
What if it's true what we sing about that Jesus rose?

05:56.331 --> 05:57.252
What if it's true?

05:57.793 --> 05:59.776
What should be the difference in our life?

05:59.856 --> 06:01.980
What difference does it make in our world?

06:02.421 --> 06:03.783
Should it affect how we live?

06:04.043 --> 06:07.709
And the obvious answer to that is yes, it should affect how you live.

06:08.109 --> 06:13.999
The sad truth is most people who declare belief in the resurrection live no differently than anyone else.

06:16.723 --> 06:21.170
When people have truly met the risen savior as Paul the Apostle shows,

06:21.922 --> 06:25.788
When they know he's alive, it changes their entire life.

06:25.889 --> 06:27.431
The question is, has it changed yours?

06:28.493 --> 06:29.254
What if it's true?

06:30.777 --> 06:36.847
Well, let me just give you a couple of answers that I've had to consider because this isn't about me pointing at you.

06:36.907 --> 06:39.251
This is about me being a part of the journey with you.

06:39.351 --> 06:45.581
And I don't know for fact that my life is a good reflection of Jesus.

06:45.621 --> 06:48.626
It should be if I really believed he was alive.

06:49.762 --> 06:50.363
What if it's true?

06:50.623 --> 06:59.752
Well, if Jesus rose from the dead, that means that we can experience a new life, every one of us.

07:00.372 --> 07:08.160
I love how Paul, the apostle said it, who wrote the wrong story with his life and messed up so profoundly by even killing Jesus followers.

07:09.341 --> 07:18.450
This is what he said in 2 Corinthians 5, 17, therefore, if anyone's in Christ, the new creation has come, the old has gone.

07:19.170 --> 07:20.812
The new is here.

07:22.273 --> 07:26.537
Well, I have to tell you that along with Paul, I've blown it profoundly.

07:27.398 --> 07:37.348
So many regrets, so much to have shame and guilt over, but because Jesus walked out of that tomb, I don't have to live in bondage to my old story.

07:37.929 --> 07:42.954
I can experience the new life of Jesus' resurrection, and so can you.

07:42.994 --> 07:44.295
What if it's true?

07:44.315 --> 07:45.796
You can have a new life.

07:46.157 --> 07:47.378
You can start over.

07:49.282 --> 07:50.323
What if it's true?

07:50.624 --> 07:56.771
Well, if Jesus really rose from the dead, it means we don't have to live or lead empty lives.

07:57.872 --> 08:03.419
Because the tomb is empty, we can experience the fullness of Jesus.

08:03.779 --> 08:09.046
If Jesus was still in the grave filling it up, we would have nothing to fill us up.

08:09.366 --> 08:12.450
We would be empty, which is where most of the world is.

08:12.570 --> 08:15.954
And sadly, most people in churches today, it's where they are.

08:17.218 --> 08:32.489
trying to find some kind of meaning and some kind of hope and some kind of peace and some kind of joy through stuff, through success, through achievement, through getting one more follower on their Instagram with their beautiful hip move.

08:32.790 --> 08:33.532
I mean, really?

08:33.552 --> 08:38.642
The more followers you have,

08:39.074 --> 08:43.840
The more you realize one more follower will just leave you as empty as you were before.

08:44.200 --> 08:45.562
It does nothing for you.

08:45.842 --> 08:55.834
But we don't have to keep living and leading empty lives because if Jesus rose from the dead, he is available and willing to fill us up.

08:56.315 --> 09:00.760
Mark 836 really points out the reality of the world without Jesus.

09:00.840 --> 09:03.503
What good is it for someone to gain the whole world?

09:04.765 --> 09:05.746
Yet lose their soul.

09:06.978 --> 09:09.201
Then Jesus said, but this is why I came into the world.

09:10.162 --> 09:17.451
John 10 10, all the thief, the evil one comes to steal, kill and destroy, to suck the very life out of you and leave you empty.

09:17.551 --> 09:22.518
But I have come to give you life in all of its fullness.

09:22.558 --> 09:23.279
What if it's true?

09:23.679 --> 09:27.744
If Jesus rose, you can experience the fullness that God intends for you.

09:28.185 --> 09:35.474
And if it's true, if Jesus really rose, you have the power available to you.

09:36.194 --> 09:44.265
to successfully live the life that God has designed for you, even in this dark, despairing, and godless world.

09:44.926 --> 09:45.887
I mean, you just do.

09:46.348 --> 09:50.032
Look at Philippians 4, 13, because Jesus is alive.

09:50.052 --> 09:53.637
I can do all this through Him who gives me strength.

09:55.019 --> 09:59.725
If Jesus was still in the grave, that verse right there would be a joke.

10:01.908 --> 10:06.194
But if the tomb is empty and Jesus alive, which He is,

10:06.658 --> 10:13.168
That means that He is available to give us the strength that we need to accomplish what God has created us for.

10:13.569 --> 10:15.492
We don't have to live in our weakness.

10:15.812 --> 10:17.014
We can live in His strength.

10:17.375 --> 10:28.872
And then first John 4-4, you, dear children, are from God and have overcome all this junk because the one who is in you is greater than the one who is in the world.

10:30.094 --> 10:32.498
If Jesus was still in the tomb, then

10:33.026 --> 10:40.118
The only thing in us would be ourselves and it would be weakness and frailty and brokenness and flaws.

10:40.218 --> 10:50.215
But if Jesus really arose from the dead, it means that He can be in us and He's greater than your biggest challenge.

10:50.255 --> 10:51.918
He's greater than your biggest obstacle.

10:51.978 --> 10:53.481
He's greater than your biggest fear.

10:53.561 --> 10:55.203
He's greater than your biggest storm.

10:55.524 --> 10:57.467
He's greater than your biggest persecution.

10:57.888 --> 10:59.090
He's greater.

10:59.394 --> 11:00.855
than the enemy of the world.

11:01.296 --> 11:03.938
And we don't have to cower and live in fear.

11:04.099 --> 11:11.706
We can stand up fearless and encourage and with hope because Jesus walked out of that tomb and he's giving his power to us.

11:12.207 --> 11:14.068
If he, yeah, you can clap if you want.

11:14.088 --> 11:14.549
That's fine.

11:17.612 --> 11:18.953
To me, I don't know if you can tell.

11:18.973 --> 11:26.601
This is an exciting message for me, but there was only one that liked it enough to clap and the rest of you gave us pity.

11:26.621 --> 11:28.082
So thank you very much for that.

11:28.802 --> 11:32.927
Maybe along the way, you'll find some excitement about it too, just kidding, just kidding.

11:33.949 --> 11:39.616
You're saying, seriously, I sat in a traffic jam to come to Northridge for Easter and you're going to beat me up for not clapping.

11:39.636 --> 11:40.677
Thank you very much, dude.

11:42.199 --> 11:45.844
Well, Jesus' resurrection gives you the power to overcome your bitterness even towards me.

11:45.964 --> 11:47.526
So that's just another thought.

11:49.288 --> 11:54.034
You can have in you the one who's greater than anything in the world.

11:54.946 --> 12:08.204
But what saddens me is that very often I cower before the life and the obstacles that I have to face instead of realizing that Jesus is bigger than any of those enemies, don't you?

12:09.125 --> 12:13.171
I don't want to sit around and sing songs about the resurrection and tell stories about it.

12:13.311 --> 12:19.339
I want to experience the power of it and all we have to do is finally say, man, I believe.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.522
What if it's true that

12:21.858 --> 12:22.559
Jesus rose.

12:22.579 --> 12:32.350
Well, if Jesus rose, it means that God has the power to turn a permanent ending into a brand new beginning.

12:33.811 --> 12:47.026
Now, for me, this is where this conversation starts really heating up because the one thing I hate more than anything else on the planet as a human being is endings.

12:48.066 --> 12:49.588
I despise endings.

12:49.908 --> 12:52.432
And that's bad for me because here's the reality.

12:52.852 --> 12:57.619
Humanity is about two things and two things only in the end.

12:58.219 --> 13:01.203
Beginnings and endings, no way around it.

13:03.186 --> 13:06.691
You're born and then sorry, you die.

13:06.711 --> 13:07.752
Ending.

13:08.673 --> 13:09.755
Beginnings and endings.

13:09.775 --> 13:10.816
I hate endings so much.

13:11.097 --> 13:12.178
I used to really...

13:12.482 --> 13:13.163
bug my wife.

13:13.583 --> 13:20.471
We would plan for a long time for a cool getaway, a cool vacation, and she would say, no, we didn't plan.

13:20.491 --> 13:21.432
I planned.

13:21.592 --> 13:24.095
So, okay, I'm a pastor, gotta have integrity.

13:24.416 --> 13:35.108
She would plan for a long time for these vacations that we were going on, and two days into the vacation, no matter how great it was, I would start getting kind of depressed.

13:36.209 --> 13:37.691
She'd go, what is going on?

13:37.711 --> 13:40.594
I said, it's gonna be over before you know it.

13:43.202 --> 13:44.624
I know how to pressing, right?

13:44.644 --> 13:46.567
I mean, seriously, what did a pressing guy?

13:46.587 --> 13:50.752
I hate endings, but you know, vacations are one thing, but in real life, it's another.

13:52.955 --> 14:00.485
When I stood at my dad's grave, that was the first time I experienced a permanent ending that changed my life forever.

14:03.089 --> 14:05.372
That was a loss that was permanent.

14:08.416 --> 14:12.882
And I don't know about you, but the grief of those kind of moments, some of you have faced

14:13.474 --> 14:19.603
job losses and relationship losses, and you know exactly the permanent ending.

14:21.766 --> 14:42.034
And if Jesus didn't walk out of that tomb, then permanent endings rationally only lead to one place, permanent grief, permanent despair, agony, bitterness, anger, which explains why our world's like our world is.

14:44.034 --> 14:46.457
endings lead to despair.

14:48.420 --> 14:49.722
But what if it's true?

14:50.803 --> 15:00.737
If Jesus rose, that means that God can take our permanent endings and make them brand new beginnings.

15:01.598 --> 15:08.607
Look at how Acts 2 says it, verse 23, this man Jesus was handed over to you by God's deliberate plan and foreknowledge.

15:08.647 --> 15:10.350
It's not an accident that he died.

15:11.732 --> 15:13.554
And you with the help of wicked men

15:13.762 --> 15:20.430
put him to death, permanent ending, by nailing him to the cross, talk about permanent.

15:22.733 --> 15:32.445
But God raised him from the dead, freeing him from the agony of death because it was impossible for death to keep its hold on him.

15:35.188 --> 15:43.058
Because Jesus walked out of that tomb and is alive, there are two words that can change our lives, but God.

15:44.162 --> 15:45.543
I don't know what you're facing right now.

15:45.703 --> 15:49.867
Some of you are probably in an agony that's beyond anything I've ever experienced.

15:51.189 --> 15:55.253
Some of you are facing really hopeless circumstances, real darkness.

15:55.913 --> 16:00.958
Your life's being turned upside down and it seems like a permanent ending and humanly it is.

16:01.439 --> 16:02.500
Nothing you can do about it.

16:04.261 --> 16:10.728
But I want you to know we're here celebrating an event that was a permanent ending, Jesus dead and in the grave.

16:12.469 --> 16:13.330
And then he walked out.

16:14.818 --> 16:22.128
which means in your circumstance, no matter how dark, you should always have hope.

16:23.851 --> 16:26.915
But God, but God.

16:27.255 --> 16:30.039
This isn't a song we sing, a holiday we celebrate.

16:30.099 --> 16:32.182
This is the reality that God provided us.

16:32.262 --> 16:37.810
God so loved us that He gave His Son, so we who could only no despair

16:37.890 --> 16:40.895
could by his grace know a brand new beginning.

16:41.256 --> 16:47.727
As we sang earlier, they laid him down inside that grave permanent ending, but that wasn't the end.

16:48.649 --> 16:56.142
We don't ever have to lose hope because Sunday is coming, a brand new beginning.

16:56.623 --> 17:00.850
I don't know what you're facing, but I know this, God is opening

17:00.962 --> 17:03.405
the door to a brand new journey.

17:03.766 --> 17:10.575
And in Christ Jesus, no matter how dark his son will always shine, you say, but we live in Michigan and the sun never shines.

17:10.616 --> 17:11.296
I get it.

17:14.561 --> 17:26.097
I've lived here a long time and I'm gonna tell you in the winter, in the cold of winter, when all of a sudden, out of nowhere, the sun shows up and it gets to like 70 degrees.

