22:35.368 --> 22:36.850
And all I found was emptiness.

22:38.351 --> 22:40.914
I was still the same miserable person within.

22:42.722 --> 22:44.424
And that's what started his journey.

22:44.524 --> 22:47.288
And his journey finally stopped when he found Jesus.

22:47.448 --> 22:55.999
And Jesus' death and burial and resurrection became the transformative truth in my dad's life.

22:56.160 --> 22:57.461
It changed his life forever.

22:59.644 --> 23:02.648
When he was 68, he got pancreatic cancer 24 years ago.

23:02.688 --> 23:03.689
That was a death sentence.

23:06.093 --> 23:07.094
And he was in the hospital.

23:07.154 --> 23:10.258
And one of my brothers and I flew down to see him immediately.

23:11.522 --> 23:17.932
My other brother was a pastor as well, and you don't believe in a miracle-working God.

23:19.154 --> 23:22.098
My dad was a lawyer, and he had two sons that became pastors.

23:22.218 --> 23:23.761
I mean, seriously, that's a miracle.

23:23.841 --> 23:28.728
But then my brother and I walked into my dad's hospital room.

23:28.748 --> 23:29.990
And remember, we were pastors.

23:30.030 --> 23:35.458
We had stood on platforms, and we had taught about the resurrection of Jesus Christ and his hope.

23:35.478 --> 23:40.626
And here we were facing our dad's permanent ending and our permanent ending with our dad.

23:40.706 --> 23:41.867
And we lost it.

23:44.570 --> 23:45.692
It was on grief.

23:48.335 --> 23:49.676
And my dad looked at us.

23:49.816 --> 23:50.878
He was the one dying.

23:50.938 --> 23:54.582
He looked at us with that stupid, far more tractor smile of his.

23:56.024 --> 23:59.768
And he said, you can't scare me with heaven, boys.

24:02.011 --> 24:05.074
Here's what happens when you know.

24:09.698 --> 24:14.224
Here's what happens when you know the risen Jesus.

24:16.326 --> 24:17.508
You still face endings.

24:18.990 --> 24:20.371
You still face disappointments.

24:22.534 --> 24:30.184
You still face hurt and betrayal and brokenness and darkness and hatred and death.

24:32.126 --> 24:36.932
But you never have to face them without hope.

24:38.114 --> 24:38.514
Never.

24:39.266 --> 24:45.353
We're celebrating the resurrection now because you, each and every one of you, need that hope.

24:45.754 --> 24:49.859
God loved you enough to give it to you, but all you have to do is choose it.

24:50.059 --> 24:51.181
You don't have to work for it.

24:51.201 --> 24:52.102
You don't have to earn it.

24:52.162 --> 24:52.903
You can't.

24:52.963 --> 25:02.595
You've already blown it, and so have I. Ephesians 2, 8, 9 says, for by God's grace are you saved through faith, which is the gift of God.

25:05.238 --> 25:08.722
You can't experience it by works, otherwise you'd be proud of yourself.

25:09.954 --> 25:15.764
We're only going to brag about one person in heaven, and that's Jesus Christ who died, was buried, and rose again.

25:15.804 --> 25:17.526
That's the only one we're going to brag about.

25:22.935 --> 25:24.197
But we will miss some people.

25:26.982 --> 25:28.444
We don't want those people to be you.

25:30.288 --> 25:30.969
I'm begging you.

25:32.411 --> 25:34.975
Put your faith in Jesus, accept the gift of God.

25:35.396 --> 25:36.658
Let him change your life.

25:37.058 --> 25:40.862
In fact, right now, before we continue in worship, would you bow your head with me just for a moment?

25:40.882 --> 25:43.345
And as we bow, I just want to encourage you.

25:43.745 --> 25:47.169
I know thousands of you are watching online, so glad you're with us.

25:47.850 --> 25:51.714
Some of you are watching at our Northridge Brighton campus, so glad you're with us.

25:52.195 --> 25:55.298
Others right here in Plymouth where I'm speaking.

25:55.338 --> 25:59.863
But I want you to know, wherever you are, if you don't know Jesus, you can right now.

25:59.883 --> 26:06.290
Take my words in this prayer and make them your words set in faith to God.

26:07.170 --> 26:14.401
Just say, Jesus, I believe that you came, that you live the perfect life I failed to live.

26:14.461 --> 26:20.871
And then on that cross, you died the death I deserve to die.

26:22.473 --> 26:26.900
But then you rose to give me new life.

26:27.100 --> 26:35.954
So I right now confess my sin, turn to you, and put my faith in your forgiveness and salvation.

26:37.314 --> 26:38.276
in Jesus' name.

26:39.838 --> 26:40.179
Amen.

26:41.440 --> 26:43.043
If you just prayed with me, let us know.

26:43.243 --> 26:51.316
We want to give you a book of the Bible that in journal form, it's a really neat little way to get to know God a little better and send you ideas for building next steps with God.

26:51.336 --> 26:52.518
And all you have to do is text us.

26:52.858 --> 26:54.040
We need to know you prayed with me.

26:54.601 --> 27:00.210
So text us to the number 31616, one word message, Northridge.

27:00.802 --> 27:04.285
And we'll send you a link, fill that out, get it back to us, we'll send you that information.

27:04.345 --> 27:06.187
But you know what you want to do?

27:06.247 --> 27:11.492
You know what you can't help doing when you meet the risen Savior?

27:12.673 --> 27:17.558
You can't help wanting to praise Him and worship Him and thank Him.

27:17.898 --> 27:20.281
And so that's what this celebration is about.

27:20.341 --> 27:23.704
So would you stand together with us right now and together?

27:24.044 --> 27:30.290
Let's worship Jesus, the risen Savior who has a name above all names.

